        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed"><strong>Technical audit tools that surface structural issues affecting your site's topical authority are available at no cost for most site sizes, making them a practical part of a free GEO stack.</strong></p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">

          <div class="card p-6">
            <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">Screaming Frog SEO Spider (Free Tier)</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-500 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">Free tier — up to 500 URLs</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300"><strong>Screaming Frog's free tier crawls up to 500 URLs and surfaces the technical issues — orphan pages, thin content, broken internal links, missing metadata — that undermine the topical authority signals AI models use when evaluating citation sources.</strong> For sites under 500 pages, the free tier is functionally complete. For larger sites, it is useful for auditing specific sections or URL patterns. Screaming Frog does not measure AI visibility directly, but it identifies the structural weaknesses in your content architecture that limit AI citation potential. It is a standard part of any GEO technical audit and available at no cost for most use cases.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-6">
            <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-50">PageSpeed Insights and Core Web Vitals</h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-500 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">Genuinely free — no usage limit</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300"><strong>Google's PageSpeed Insights and Core Web Vitals tooling are free and relevant to GEO in that technical page quality is a prerequisite for AI citation consideration.</strong> A page that loads poorly, is inaccessible, or fails basic technical standards is less likely to be indexed and referenced by AI retrieval systems. These tools identify the technical baseline issues that should be resolved before investing in GEO-specific optimisation. They address a necessary but not sufficient condition: fixing Core Web Vitals will not drive AI citations on its own, but persistent technical failures create a ceiling on the impact of content optimisation work.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
